e":"Lecomte","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Monique, Normand, Alain, Armand, Cecile, Dominique, Francois, Germain, Gilles, Gregoire, Huguette, Pierre.","French and Walloon: nickname for someone in the service of a count or for someone who behaved pretentiously, from Old French <i>conte</i>, <i>cunte</i> ‘count’, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>. Compare   Comte   1.","History: This surname is listed (in the form <i>Le Comte</i>) in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."],"variants":[{"name":"Leconte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Andre, Fritz, Herve, Jean Louis, Pierre, Raoul, Raynald, Rommel, Wesner, Yves.","French: variant of   Lecomte   ‘the count’ (see   Comte   1). This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Conte   3 and   Laconte  .","History: This surname is listed (in the form <i>Le Conte</i>) in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Lecompte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andrus, Emile, Adelard, Armand, Elrick, Julien, Laurent, Leonce, Marcel, Monique, Normand.","French: variant of   Lecomte   ‘the count’. Compare   Lacount   and   Lecount  .","History: This surname is listed (in the form <i>Le Compte</i>) in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Comte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Jean Jacques.","French:","nickname for someone in the service of a count or for someone who behaved pretentiously, from Old French <i>conte</i>, <i>cunte</i> ‘count’. In North America, this surname is also a shortened form of the French cognate   Lecomte  . Compare   Conte   3."]}]},{"name":"Demange","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre.","French: from a regional variant of the personal name   Dominique  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Demanche","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Cecile, Marcel, Michel, Normand.","French: variant of   Demange   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."]},{"name":"Dominique","meanings":["Feminine form of   Dominic  , from a French form that is used as both a girl's and a boy's name."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1670184,"age":0,"year":"1598","julianDay":2304718,"title":"Edict of Nantes ","description":"Under the rule of Henry IV of France the Edict of Nantes was issued giving the people some religious liberty. The edict brought an end to the religious wars that were going on at the time. ","url":"https://www.britannica.com/event/Edict-of-Nantes","urlTitle":"Encyclopedia Britannica- Edict of Nantes","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1355839,"age":12,"year":"1610","julianDay":2309101,"description":"Reigns of Louis XIII and Louis XIV. Royal power at its peak. France dominates Europe, French culture spreads. Start of large-scale sea trade.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1670166,"age":84,"year":"1682","julianDay":2335399,"title":"The Palace of Versailles","description":"The Palace of Versailles was originally known as a hunting log and retreat for Louis XII. When Louis XIV took over he moved his family into it. After he died the palace was abandoned. It has since been turned into a museum.","url":"https://www.britannica.com/topic/Palace-of-Versailles","urlTitle":"Encyclopedia Britannica- Palace of Versailles","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1670191,"age":102,"year":"1700","toYear":"1792","julianDay":2341973,"title":"French Monarchy","description":"The French monarchy started way before the 1700s, but for the most part the major events of history took place during this time before the French Revolution started. This was known as the Bourbon Dynasty. Louis XIV the Great, Louis XV the Beloved, Louis XVI the Restorer of French Liberty, and Louis XVII all reigned during this time.","url":"https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmXoypizjW3WknFiJnKLwHCnL72vedxjQkDDP1mXWo6uco/wiki/Kingdom_of_France.html","urlTitle":"Kingdom of France","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"When Demange Lecomte was born in 1598, in Vexaincourt, Vosges, Lorraine, France, his father, Demange LECOMTE, was 29 and his mother, Marie Duxey, was 29. He married Eve Colin on 16 September 1624, in Luvigny, Vosges, Grand Est, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1598–":"1598–Surnud","1598–Male":"1598–Surnud","1603–Female":"1603–Surnud","1630–1683":"1630–1683","1570–Male":"1570–Surnud","1570–Female":"1570–Surnud","1700":"1700","1610":"1610","1598":"1598","1630":"1630","16 septembre 1624":"16. september 1624","1683":"1683","1792":"1792","1682":"1682","1570":"1570","1603":"1603","Raon-sur-Plaine,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-sur-Plaine, Vosges, Grand Est, Prantsusmaa","Vexaincourt,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Vexaincourt, Vosges, Lorraine, Prantsusmaa","Luvigny, Vosges, Lorraine, France":"Luvigny, Vosges, Grand Est, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1598–":"1598–Kuollut","1598–Male":"1598–Kuollut","1603–Female":"1603–Kuollut","1630–1683":"1630–1683","1570–Male":"1570–Kuollut","1570–Female":"1570–Kuollut","1700":"1700","1610":"1610","1598":"1598","1630":"1630","16 septembre 1624":"16. syyskuuta 1624","1683":"1683","1792":"1792","1682":"1682","1570":"1570","1603":"1603","Raon-sur-Plaine,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-sur-Plaine, Vosges, Grand Est, Ranska","Vexaincourt,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Vexaincourt, Vosges, Lorraine, Ranska","Luvigny, Vosges, Lorraine, France":"Luvigny, Vosges, Grand Est, Ranska"},"fr":{"1598–":"1598–Décédé","1598–Male":"1598–Décédé","1603–Female":"1603–Décédée","1630–1683":"1630–1683","1570–Male":"1570–Décédé","1570–Female":"1570–Décédée","1700":"1700"